{{see also|Akdağ (surname)}}
'''Akdağ''' ({{lang-tr|Akdağ}}, "white mountain") is the name of several different mountains in [[Turkey]].

One of them is in the [[Çameli]] district of [[Denizli Province]], and in the [[Çivril]] district of [[Afyon Province]]. It is located at the western end of the [[Taurus Mountains]] in Aegean Region of Turkey. Its highest peak is 3,213 m. The area was declared a national park in 2000.<ref>[http://www.kultur.gov.tr/EN/BelgeGoster.aspx?17A16AE30572D3137EE1F1486EE5030EC2D66D0CC5B52EB8 Republic of Turkey Ministry of Culture and Tourism], "Afyon - Akdağ National Park".</ref>

There are also mountains named Akdağ in [[Sivas Province|Sivas]] and [[Burdur Province|Burdur]] provinces.

