{{unreferenced|date=June 2014}} [[Image:Giebichenstein.jpg|right|thumbnail|250px|The "Giebichenstein" in [[Stöckse]], Germany]]
The '''Giebichenstein''' in [[Stöckse]], Germany, is one of the largest [[Glacial erratic|erratic boulders]] of northern Germany. A picture of the Giebichenstein is part of the emblem of the Stöckse municipality.
There is the supposition that during [[Wolstonian Stage]] the stone was deposited by glaciers as a part of a [[moraine]]. Near the Giebichenstein there are the remains of a [[dolmen]], and at the stone itself there were found the remains of a [[stone age]] hunter's camp.
