In [[power engineering]], '''Kron reduction''' is a method used to reduce or eliminate the desired node without need of repeating the steps like in [[Gaussian elimination]].<ref>{{Cite journal | url=https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0005109814003331 | doi=10.1016/j.automatica.2014.08.017| title=Towards Kron reduction of generalized electrical networks| journal=Automatica| volume=50| issue=10| pages=2586–2590| year=2014| last1=Caliskan| first1=Sina Yamac| last2=Tabuada| first2=Paulo}}</ref> 

It is named after American [[electrical engineer]] [[Gabriel Kron]].

